}}'''舒沙大屠杀'''發生於1920年3月22日至26日，在[[亞美尼亞人|亞美尼亞人]]針對[[亞塞拜然民主共和國|亞塞拜然民主共和國]]的反抗被镇压后，[[亞塞拜然民主共和國|亞塞拜然民主共和國]]對位於[[舒沙|舒沙]]的亚美尼亚人进行大规模的杀戮，消滅了[[舒沙|舒沙]]一半的亚美尼亚人，並摧毀大量亚美尼亚人的居住区。<ref>S. Neil MacFarlane, Oliver Thränert,, ''Balancing hegemony: the OSCE in the CIS'', Centre for International Relations, 1997, p. [https://books.google.com/books?id=KEshAQAAIAAJ 71] "Another event of the period was the massacre in March 1920 of Armenians in Shusha, the historic centre of Karabakh, which shifted its ethnic status from an Armenian-dominated town to an Azeri-dominated one."</ref><ref>{{Cite book|last=Brook|first=Stephen|title=Claws of the crab: Georgia and Armenia in crisis|year=1993|page=[https://books.google.com/books?id=fUMjAQAAMAAJ& 326]|quote=In the 1920s a massacre of Armenians led to an Azeri majority in the town.}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|last=Chorbajian|first=Levon|title=The Caucasian Knot: The History & Geopolitics of Nagorno-Karabagh|year=1994|publisher=Zed Books|location=London|isbn=9781856492881|page=141|quote=The city of Shushi, formerly the third largest city in Transcaucasia, saw its Armenian population decimated by the massacre of March 1920.}}</ref><ref> A. Zubov, [http://magazines.russ.ru/znamia/2000/4/zubov.html Политическое будущее Кавказа: опыт ретроспективно-сравнительного анализа (Political future of the Caucasus)],"Znamiya" journal, 2000, #4 "Британская администрация почему-то передала населенные армянами уезды Елизаветпольской губернии под юрисдикцию Азербайджана. Британский администратор Карабаха полковник Шательворт не препятствовал притеснениям армян, чинимым татарской администрацией губернатора Салтанова. Межнациональные трения завершились страшной резней, в которой погибла большая часть армян города Шуши. Бакинский парламент отказался даже осудить свершителей Шушинской резни, и в Карабахе вспыхнула война." <br /><br /> "The British administrator of Karabakh, Colonel D.I. Shuttleworth did not interfere with the discrimination of Armenians by [[鞑靼人|Tatarian]] administration of governor Saltanov. The national clashes ended by the terrible massacres in which the most of Armenians in Shusha town perished. The Parliament in [[巴库|Baku]] refused even condemn the accomplishers of the massacres in Shusha and the war was started in Karabakh."</ref><ref>{{Citation|title=Armenia in Crisis: The 1988 Earthquake|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Y4kQUU_bpOsC|last=Verluise|first=Pierre|date=April 1995|publisher={{link-en|Wayne State University Press}}|page=6|isbn=0814325270}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Situation des réfugiés et déplacés d'origine arménienne sur le territoire de l'ex-Union soviétique|url=http://www.commission-refugies.fr/IMG/pdf/Ex-URSS_-_situation_des_refugies_et_deplaces_d_origine_armenienne_sur_le_territoire_de_l_ex-Union_sovietique.pdf|work={{link-en|Commission des recours des refugies}}|language=fr|quote=De 1918 à 1920, les républiques indépendantes d'Arménie et d'Azerbaïdjan se sont disputées le contrôle du Karabagh, pour des raisons symboliques et stratégiques. Des pogroms et des incendies anéantissent le quartier arménien de Chouchi en février 1920.}}</ref>

